{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The suit is following a trend so pronounced that it has sometimes displaced attempts to remedy the discriminatory treatment itself....", "abstract": "Former Fox News anchor Gretchen Carlson's complaint of sexual harassment by chairman Roger Ailes is centered mostly on her claims that he retaliated against her after she stood up to him, not on underlying discrimination; some legal experts note more workers are bringing retaliation claims, which are often easier to prove than bias, but may not remedy discrimination.", "section_name": "Business Day", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Noam", "role": "reported", "lastname": "SCHEIBER", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By NOAM SCHEIBER"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/09/business/gretchen-carlson-suit-aims-at-retaliation-over-discrimination.html", "lead_paragraph": "The suit is following a trend so pronounced that it has sometimes displaced attempts to remedy the discriminatory treatment itself.", "headline": {"main": "Gretchen Carlson Suit Aims at Retaliation Over Discrimination", "print_headline": "Claim of Retaliation at Fox Could Leave Bias in Place"}, "_id": "577ff88b38f0d8706f764146", "word_count": "1070", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2016/07/09/business/09WORKPLACE/09WORKPLACE-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2016/07/09/business/09WORKPLACE/09WORKPLACE-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2016/07/09/business/09WORKPLACE/09WORKPLACE-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/07/09/business/09WORKPLACE/09WORKPLACE-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2016/07/09/business/09WORKPLACE/09WORKPLACE-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2016/07/09/b